"{\"uid\": \"si.com-olympics-american-section-fancy-french-grocery-store-paris-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"PARIS \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094 It\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s important to see the sites when you are traveling, so after checking out the Eiffel Tower and the Picasso Museum, I recently made my way to my favorite Paris landmark: the American food section of the city\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s fanciest grocery store.\\u00c2  La Grande \\u00c3\\u0089picerie, about a mile east of where archery is being contested at the complex that houses Napoleon\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s tomb, is the grocery store attached to Le Bon March\\u00c3\\u00a9, a high-end department store owned by LVMH, which also owns Louis Vuitton, Moet-Hennessy and Tiffany.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 523, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 115, \"end\": 129, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Museu_Picasso\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.29109835943458e-24, \"text\": \"Picasso Museum\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\", \"Q33506\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Museu_Picasso\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Museu_Picasso\"}, {\"begin\": 169, \"end\": 174, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999736247, \"rank\": 2.6813870499566968e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 189, \"end\": 197, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999551551142095, \"rank\": 4.484687892821436e-05, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 460, \"end\": 464, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LVMH\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.58653545967347e-33, \"text\": \"LVMH\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LVMH\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LVMH\"}, {\"begin\": 482, \"end\": 495, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis_Vuitton\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1561095402685587e-33, \"text\": \"Louis Vuitton\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis_Vuitton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louis_Vuitton\"}, {\"begin\": 515, \"end\": 522, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tiffany_Darwish\", \"score\": 0.9114667272837185, \"rank\": 0.09405615855014472, \"text\": \"Tiffany\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tiffany_Darwish\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tiffany_Darwish\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"La Grande \\u00c3\\u0089picerie mostly matches its LVMH siblings in luxury, from the multiple foie gras refrigerators to the cheese counter that almost needs its own postcode.\", \"from\": 525, \"to\": 688, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 607, \"end\": 616, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Foie_gras\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3496202671841397e-56, \"text\": \"foie gras\", \"types\": [\"Q2095\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Foie_gras\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Foie_gras\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Near the produce stands a series of shelves housing international foods.\", \"from\": 689, \"to\": 761, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Italy: pasta, tomato sauce, biscotti.\", \"from\": 762, \"to\": 799, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 762, \"end\": 767, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"score\": 0.9999999999508873, \"rank\": 4.8730738253829265e-11, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Japan: nori, rice crackers, miso paste.\", \"from\": 800, \"to\": 839, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 800, \"end\": 805, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"score\": 0.9999999020883527, \"rank\": 9.706316813624276e-08, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Canada: maple syrup, maple jelly, maple sugar.\\u00c2  In the center lurks the United States, represented here by what the French seem to believe to be our national delicacies: Reese\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s, marshmallow fluff and two varieties of corn syrup.\", \"from\": 840, \"to\": 1072, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 840, \"end\": 846, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8990750282711484e-15, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada\"}, {\"begin\": 913, \"end\": 926, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.444802509970505e-14, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 957, \"end\": 963, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9999994083238494, \"rank\": 5.905362874313656e-07, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There are also half a dozen types of microwave popcorn, sour candy, off-brand boxed macaroni and cheese, jars of \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009chot-dog sausages\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d and Hershey\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s cookies and cream bars.\\u00c2  Again, this is a gourmet grocery store.\\u00c2  As an American, I am offended.\", \"from\": 1073, \"to\": 1323, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1299, \"end\": 1307, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999551551142095, \"rank\": 4.484687892821436e-05, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As a journalist, I am intrigued.\\u00c2  I stop by this area nearly every time I am in the city, hoping to see someone purchase something so I can ask why, but I have never been lucky.\", \"from\": 1324, \"to\": 1502, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Until today, when within a few minutes of lurking I caught sight of a young French woman plucking a package of Reese\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s dipped pretzels from the shelf.\", \"from\": 1503, \"to\": 1655, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1579, \"end\": 1585, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9999994083238494, \"rank\": 5.905362874313656e-07, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I pounced.\\u00c2  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s a mix of sweet and salty, and Americans love sweet and salty,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Juliette Sabater, who works in marketing, explains in French.\", \"from\": 1656, \"to\": 1805, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1744, \"end\": 1752, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Juliet\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.215672504084954e-18, \"text\": \"Juliette\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Juliet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Juliet\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Most of what is on offer here is too sweet for her, she adds.\", \"from\": 1806, \"to\": 1867, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Yes, that is our primary reputation abroad, and it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s earned:Accordingto a 2015 study by the market research firm Euromonitor, Americans average more than 126 grams of sugar per day, nearly twice the French intake\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094and more than twice the World Health Organization\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s recommendation.\\u00c2  We are perhaps not helping our cause right now with the Krispy Kreme ads throughout the Paris Metro system that bear a photo of a donut with a bite taken out of it, making it look crescent-shaped, and the caption:The best croissant in Paris.\", \"from\": 1869, \"to\": 2399, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2070, \"end\": 2076, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9999994083238494, \"rank\": 5.905362874313656e-07, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2246, \"end\": 2257, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris_M\\u00e9tro\", \"score\": 0.9999998407884176, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Metro\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris_M\\u00e9tro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris_M\\u00e9tro\"}, {\"begin\": 2393, \"end\": 2398, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999736247, \"rank\": 2.6813870499566968e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, two American tourists, teachers in New Jersey, are walking by and chuckling about the selection.\", \"from\": 2401, \"to\": 2508, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2416, \"end\": 2424, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999551551142095, \"rank\": 4.484687892821436e-05, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2447, \"end\": 2457, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Jersey\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.267678998718347e-14, \"text\": \"New Jersey\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Jersey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Jersey\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s all crap,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d says Michael Fleming with a laugh.\", \"from\": 2509, \"to\": 2566, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2537, \"end\": 2552, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Anthony_Fleming\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.5432704337009585e-15, \"text\": \"Michael Fleming\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Anthony_Fleming\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Anthony_Fleming\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He adds that when he spent time in the United Kingdom, he noticed that locals were very interested in chocolate syrup and brown sugar.\", \"from\": 2567, \"to\": 2701, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2606, \"end\": 2620, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.9309367560727423e-17, \"text\": \"United Kingdom\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But at least those are ingredients.\", \"from\": 2702, \"to\": 2737, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"These are finished products, although it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s hard to imagine finishing some of them.\\u00c2  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI think it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s kind of strange,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d says Katie Laurino.\", \"from\": 2738, \"to\": 2882, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2874, \"end\": 2881, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laurino\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Laurino\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laurino\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laurino\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI don\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t wish I had some \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0098hot-dog sausages\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 in a jar.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  C\\u00c3\\u00a9cile Irtelli, who helps select the products for the U.K. section\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094mostly teas, although they also get a dozen varieties of shortbread and a few other desserts\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094insists that that attitude is the minority.\\u00c2  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThese are very popular,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d she says in French.\", \"from\": 2883, \"to\": 3209, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3004, \"end\": 3008, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9866293747909269, \"rank\": 0.013551821535832792, \"text\": \"U.K.\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 3202, \"end\": 3208, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9999994083238494, \"rank\": 5.905362874313656e-07, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cWe have French people who come from all over France.\", \"from\": 3210, \"to\": 3265, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3221, \"end\": 3234, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French people\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}, {\"begin\": 3258, \"end\": 3264, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999999954525, \"rank\": 2.0750614255716334e-12, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You can\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t find these products elsewhere.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Beef jerky, she says, drives people especially mad.\", \"from\": 3266, \"to\": 3363, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cWe don\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t have it at all in France.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  French people understand that there is more to American food than partially hydrogenated soybean oil, explains Christy Shields, an associate professor of anthropology at the American University of Paris who specializes in the study of food.\", \"from\": 3364, \"to\": 3648, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3408, \"end\": 3421, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French people\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}, {\"begin\": 3455, \"end\": 3463, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999551551142095, \"rank\": 4.484687892821436e-05, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cyou still have the stereotype that Americans eat a bunch of junk and they eat a lot of it.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d (Speaking of stereotypes, I also emailed an associate professor who teaches a food culture class at the Sorbonne.\", \"from\": 3649, \"to\": 3863, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Her autoreply promised to get back to me some time in September.)\", \"from\": 3864, \"to\": 3929, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As more French people travel to the United States\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094at any given moment there seems to be more French than English spoken in Central Park\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094they return with an appreciation for what they have eaten there, and they bring it back with them.\", \"from\": 3931, \"to\": 4169, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3939, \"end\": 3952, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French people\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThere are a growing number of Mexican-American restaurants,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Shields says.\", \"from\": 4170, \"to\": 4249, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4203, \"end\": 4219, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mexican_Americans\", \"score\": 0.9999363953603816, \"rank\": 6.360868572326893e-05, \"text\": \"Mexican-American\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mexican_Americans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mexican_Americans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThere\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s a fascination with soul food.\", \"from\": 4250, \"to\": 4292, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There are burgers in every restaurant and caf\\u00c3\\u00a9 now.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d And another American import has taken hold: \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cOh my God,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d she says.\", \"from\": 4293, \"to\": 4419, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4361, \"end\": 4369, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999551551142095, \"rank\": 4.484687892821436e-05, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThe brunch.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Some of our cultural quirks have been less successful.\", \"from\": 4420, \"to\": 4493, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I tell Irtelli the story of when I studied abroad here and my host family welcomed me with a small jar of peanut butter (bought at a sadly defunct American food store called Thanksgiving).\", \"from\": 4494, \"to\": 4682, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4641, \"end\": 4649, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999551551142095, \"rank\": 4.484687892821436e-05, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Their only request: that I not defile their jelly with it.\", \"from\": 4683, \"to\": 4741, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Irtelli gasps at the very idea.\\u00c2  But Shields was delighted when she recently learned of a store a mile and a half east of La Grande \\u00c3\\u0089picerie called COW: Cheese of the World.\", \"from\": 4742, \"to\": 4917, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4892, \"end\": 4895, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Computer_Originated_World\", \"score\": 0.9999999999427018, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"COW\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Computer_Originated_World\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Computer_Originated_World\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It stocks a wonderful ch\\u00c3\\u00a8vre from Vermont.\", \"from\": 4918, \"to\": 4961, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4953, \"end\": 4960, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vermont\", \"score\": 0.9716450458520319, \"rank\": 0.029182420286966014, \"text\": \"Vermont\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vermont\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vermont\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI was so happy to find an American product that was artisanal,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d she says.\\u00c2  Those are in short supply at La Grande \\u00c3\\u0089picerie.\", \"from\": 4962, \"to\": 5092, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4991, \"end\": 4999, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999551551142095, \"rank\": 4.484687892821436e-05, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The closest thing I find to a mom-and-pop producer is Paul Newman\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s ranch dressing.\", \"from\": 5093, \"to\": 5178, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"While I am investigating it, Sabater reconsiders her purchase.\", \"from\": 5179, \"to\": 5241, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She returns the Reese\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s pretzels.\", \"from\": 5242, \"to\": 5277, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead she selects what appears to me to be an almost identical product by Flipz\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094from the U.K. section.\\u00c2  Stephanie Apstein is a senior writer covering baseball and Olympic sports for Sports Illustrated, where she started as an intern in 2011.\", \"from\": 5278, \"to\": 5524, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5371, \"end\": 5375, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9866293747909269, \"rank\": 0.013551821535832792, \"text\": \"U.K.\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 5387, \"end\": 5396, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephanie_Plum\", \"score\": 0.9999991443795829, \"rank\": 8.556206222102718e-07, \"text\": \"Stephanie\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephanie_Plum\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephanie_Plum\"}, {\"begin\": 5465, \"end\": 5483, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0751107120897848e-19, \"text\": \"Sports Illustrated\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She has covered 10 World Series and three Olympics, and is a frequent contributor to SportsNet New York's Baseball Night in New York.\", \"from\": 5525, \"to\": 5658, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5610, \"end\": 5628, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/SNY_(TV_network)\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"SportsNet N